he%20institution%20in%20the%201930s%20and%2040s%2C%20per%20the%20Post's%20sprawling%20investigation%2C%20based%20on%20Smithsonian%20Records%20obtained%20by%20the%20Post.%20The%20Natural%20History%20Museum%20still%20holds%20254%20in%20Maryland%20in%20a%20storage%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fblogs%2Foffice-of-the-secretary-of-the-smithsonian%2F2023%2F11%2F30%2Fwhat-comes-next-smithsonian-new-human-remains-task-force%2F%3Fitid%3Dlk_inline_enhanced-template%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20published%20in%20late%20November%20by%20historian%20and%20Smithsonian%20Institution%20secretary%20Lonnie%20Bunch%20III%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20museum%20said%20it%20was%20working%20to%20%26quot%3Brectify%20these%20wrongs%26quot%3B%20and%20prevent%20their%20recurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20practice%20can%20reveal%20critical%20details%20about%20past%20civilizations%2C%20it%20now%20comes%20with%20a%20host%20of%20ethical%20considerations%2C%20which%20have%20significantly%20changed%20the%20scientific%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Bunch%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20remains%20still%20in%20our%20possession%20were%20acquired%20decades%20ago%20without%20the%20proper%20consent%20of%20the%20individuals%2C%20their%20close%20relatives%20or%20their%20tribal%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Institution%20also%20announced%20a%20task%20force%20dedicated%20to%20finding%20recommendations%20for%20the%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20added%20that%20the%201989%20passage%20of%20the%20National%20Museum%20of%20the%20American%20Indian%20Act%20had%20facilitated%20the%20repatriation%20of%20thousands%20of%20other%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20challenging%20task%20involves%20using%20the%20limited%20records%20we%20have%20to%20identify%20who%20these%20people%20were%20and%20who%20their%20surviving%20relatives%20might%20be.%20When%20it's%20not%20possible%20to%20identify%20a%20direct%2