%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67715933%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67715933.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67715933.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20Prince%20Harry's%20Phone%20Hacking%20Lawsuit%20Against%20UK%20Tabloid%20Group%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20overseeing%20the%20phone-hacking%20and%20privacy%20lawsuit%20brought%20by%20Prince%20Harry%20and%20some%20100%20others%20against%20British%20publisher%20Mirror%20Group%20Newspapers%20(MGN)%20at%20London's%20High%20Court%20will%20deliver%20his%20judgment%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20details%20of%20the%20case%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20case%20about%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarry%20and%20100%20others%20sued%20MGN%2C%20publisher%20of%20the%20Daily%20Mirror%2C%20the%20Sunday%20Mirror%20and%20the%20Sunday%20People%20tabloids%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%20widespread%20unlawful%20activities%20between%201991%20and%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20involved%20in%20the%20case%20include%20actors%2C%20sports%20stars%2C%20celebrities%20and%20people%20who%20simply%20had%20a%20connection%20to%20high-profile%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20accuse%20the%20media%20group's%20journalists%20or%20private%20investigators%20of%20phone-hacking%20on%20an%20%26quot%3Bindustrial%20scale%26quot%3B%20and%20obtaining%20private%20details%20by%20deception%20and%20say%20that%20senior%20editors%20and%20executives%20knew%20and%20approved%20of%20such%20behaviour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMGN%2C%20owned%20by%20Reach%2C%20contested%20the%20claims%20and%20denied%20senior%20figures%20were%20aware%20of%20wrongdoing.%20It%20also%20argued%20that%20some%20of%20the%20lawsuits%20were%20brought%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarry%2C%20the%20younger%20son%20of%20King%20Charles%2C%20was%20selected%20as%20one%20of%20the%20four%20test%20cases%20for%20the%20trial%20which%20began%20last%20May.%20He%20is%20seeking%20up%20to%20320%2C000%20(%24405%2C000)%20pounds%20in%20damages%20over%2033%20articles%20considered%20at%20the%20trial%2C%20plus%20a%20further%20120%2C000%20pounds%20for%2061%20episodes%20of%20alleged%20unlawful%20information-gathering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMGN%20has%20admitted%20private%20investigators%20had%20been%20instructed%20to%20unlawfully%20gather%20information%20about%20three%20of%20those%20involved%20in%20the%20test%20cases%2C%20including%2C%20on%20one%20occasion%2C%20Harry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20publisher%20said%20it%20unreservedly%20apologised%20and%20that%20the%20prince%20was%20entitled%20to%20500%20pounds%20in%20compensation.%20It%20denied%20any%20other%20wrongdoing%20about%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20phone%20hacking%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhone%20hacking%2C%20the%20illegal%20interception%20of%20voicemails%20on%20mobile%20phones%2C%20first%20came%20to%20public%20attention%20in%202006%20when%20the%20then-royal%20editor%20of%20the%20News%20of%20the%20World%20(NoW)%20tabloid%20and%20a%20private%20investigator%20were%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20pleaded%20guilty%20and%20were%20jailed%20in%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202011%20further%20revelations%20emerged%2C%20including%20that%20a%20murdered%20schoolgirl%20had%20been%20targeted%2C%20leading%20to%20Rupert%20Murdoch%20closing%20the%20paper%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20criminal%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20NoW's%20former%20editor%2C%20Andy%20Coulson%2C%20who%20later%20worked%20for%20then-Prime%20Minister%20David%20Cameron%2C%20was%20found%20guilty%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20hack%20phones%20and%20jailed.%20Rebekah%20Brooks%2C%20who%20heads%20up%20News%20Corp's%20UK%20operation%2C%20was%20acquitted%20of%20all%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mirror%20group%20had%20consistently%20denied%20its%20journalists%20had%20been%20involved%20in%20hacking%2C%20including%20at%20a%20public%20inquiry.%20But%20in%202014%2C%20it%20admitted%20liability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20MGN%20has%20settled%20more%20than%20600%20claims%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20around%20106%20million%20pounds%20in%20damages%20and%20costs%2C%2055%20million%20pounds%20of%20which%20MGN%20says%20has%20gone%20to%20the%20claimants'%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20Harry%20say%20in%20court%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Duke%20of%20Sussex%2C%20the%20fifth-in-line%20to%20the%20throne%2C%20became%20the%20first%20British%20royal%20to%20appear%20in%20the%20witness%20box%20since%20the%201890s%20when%20he%20gave%20evidence%20over%20two%20days%20at%20the%20start%20of%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarry%20said%20he%20was%20targeted%20by%20MGN%20for%2015%20years%20from%201996%20with%20more%20than%20140%20stories%20which%20appeared%20in%20its%20papers%20being%20the%20result%20of%20phone-hacking%20or%20other%20unlawful%20behaviour%2C%20although%20the%20trial%20only%20considered%2033%20of%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20blamed%20the%20intrusion%20for%20the%20breakdown%20of%20his%20relationship%20with%20a%20long-term%20girlfriend%2C%20Chelsy%20Davy%2C%20and%20said%20MGN%20had%20sown%20distrust%20in%20Harry's%20relationship%20with%20his%20elder%20brother%20Prince%20William%2C%20with%20whom%20he%20has%20since%20fallen%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Green%2C%20MGN's%20lawyer%2C%20suggested%20some%20of%20the%20personal%20information%20in%20the%20stories%20had%20come%20from%2C%20or%20was%20given%20with%20the%20consent%20of%2C%20senior%20Buckingham%20Palace%20aides%2C%20or%20was%20simply%20based%20on%20details%20already%20made%20public%20in%20other%20articles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPiers%20Morgan%20Involved%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20witnesses%2C%20including%20Harry%20himself%2C%20implicated%20senior%20figures%20from%20MGN%20as%20being%20involved%20in%20phone%20hacking%20or%20at%20least%20aware%20it%20was%20going%20on.%20The%20most%20notable%20was%20Piers%20Morgan%2C%20now%20a%20high-profile%20TV%20presenter%2C%20who%20edited%20the%20paper%20between%201995%20and%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mirror's%20former%20Group%20Political%20Editor%20David%20Seymour%20and%20Omid%20Scobie%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20tabloid%20and%20has%20recently%20made%20headlines%20with%20a%20book%20about%20the%20royal%20family%2C%20were%20among%20those%20who%20pointed%20the%20finger%20at%20Morgan%20in%20their%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMorgan%20has%20always%20denied%20any%20involvement%20in%2C%20or%20knowledge%20of%2C%20phone%20hacking%20and%20said%20he%20would%20not%20%26quot%3Btake%20lectures%20on%20privacy%20invasion%20from%20Prince%20Harry%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%2C%20Timothy%20Fancourt%2C%20queried%20whether%20Morgan%20should%20have%20given%20evidence.%20MGN's%20lawyer%20Green%20said%20calling%20Morgan%20as%20a%20witness%20would%20have%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bdisproportionate%20and%20unnecessary%26quot%3B%20sideshow%2C%20and%20the%20accusations%20against%20him%20were%20irrelevant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20else%20is%20Prince%20Harry%20suing%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20is%20one%20of%20four%20that%20Harry%20is%20pursuing%20at%20London's%20High%20Court.%20He%20is%20also%20suing%20News%20Corp's%20UK%20operation%2C%20News%20Group%20Newspapers%20(NGN)%2C%20which%20publishes%20the%20Sun%20tabloid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20singer%20Elton%20John%20and%20five%20others%2C%20he%20is%20suing%20Associated%20Newspapers%20(ANL)%2C%20publisher%20of%20the%20Daily%20Mail%20and%20Mail%20on%20Sunday%2C%20over%20alleged%20phone%20hacking%20and%20illicit%20privacy%20breaches.%20Harry%20is%20also%20suing%20ANL%20for%20libel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22p