how%2F106005332.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-may-test-icbm-soon-south-official-says-ahead-of-nuclear-talks-in-dc%2Famp_articleshow%2F106005332.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20How%20F-16%20Jets%20Can%20Reshape%20Ukraine's%20Aerial%20Battlefield%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20U.S.-made%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20for%20Ukraine%20arrive%20at%20training%20centres%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Europe%2C%20Kyiv's%20allies%20hope%20the%20modern%20aircraft%20can%20push%20Russian%20planes%20farther%20from%20the%20frontlines%2C%20target%20radar%20transmitters%20more%20effectively%20and%20hunt%20down%20more%20cruise%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommander%20in%20Chief%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Armed%20Forces%20Valery%20Zaluzhnyi%20said%20in%20November%20that%20F-16s%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bless%20helpful%26quot%3B%20now%20than%20they%20would%20have%20been%20a%20year%20ago%20because%20Russia%20has%20had%20time%20to%20improve%20its%20air%20defences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20will%20help%20address%20a%20problem%20that%20has%20persisted%20from%20the%20start%20of%20the%20invasion%20in%20February%202022%3A%20Russia's%20more%20modern%20combat%20aircraft%20have%20been%20difficult%20for%20Ukraine's%20military%20to%20counter%20with%20its%20ageing%20fighters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20examined%20technical%20documents%20and%20spoke%20to%20eight%20military%20experts%2C%20including%20former%20F-16%20trainers%20and%20pilots%2C%20about%20the%20jets'%20capabilities%2C%20limitations%20and%20the%20impact%20they%20could%20have%20on%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWestern%20military%20officials%20and%20experts%20say%20adding%20F-16s%20to%20Ukraine's%20fleet%20will%20not%20abruptly%20change%20the%20course%20of%20the%20war.%20Training%20pilots%20and%20support%20crews%20take%20time%2C%20surface-to-air%20missiles%20remain%20a%20major%20threat%2C%20and%20the%20jets%20are%20not%20designed%20for%20Ukraine's%20damaged%20and%20sometimes%20makeshift%20runways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20are%20an%20improvement%20on%20the%20closest%20equivalent%20Ukraine%20has%20-%20the%20Soviet-designed%20MiG-29%20-%20and%2C%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20will%20help%20Kyiv%20integrate%20with%20Western%20military%20allies%20and%20break%20away%20from%20reliance%20on%20ageing%20hardware%20built%20by%20its%20enemy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20locks%20Ukraine%20onto%20a%20technological%20path%20that%20NATO%20is%20currently%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robert%20Farley%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kentucky%20who%20specializes%20in%20military%20affairs%20and%20airpower.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20Ukraine%20has%20now%20is%20a%20dead%20end%3B%20It's%20not%20going%20anywhere.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20have%20an%20Air%20Force%20in%2010%20years%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20F-16s%20or%20something%20similar.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Impact%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fighters%20will%20replace%20Ukraine's%20strained%20and%20thinning%20fleet%20of%20MiG-29s%2C%20Su-24s%20and%20Su-25s%2C%20jets%20that%20came%20of%20age%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20Cold%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20found%20novel%20ways%20to%20integrate%20Western%20weapons%20into%20those%20aircraft.%20F-16s%20will%20allow%20Ukraine's%20military%20to%20squeeze%20more%20performance%20out%20of%20such%20systems%2C%20said%20Brynn%20Tannehill%2C%20a%20former%20U.S.%20Navy%20pilot%20who%20helped%20train%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20F-16%20pilots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20is%20the%20AIM-120%20Advanced%20Medium-Range%20Air-to-Air%20Missile%20(AMRAAM)%2C%20which%20Ukraine%20uses%20in%20a%20ground-launched%20anti-air%20role%20now%2C%20and%20which%20will%20soon%20be%20provided%20for%20air-to-air%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AMRAAM%20C%20and%20D%20models%20heading%20to%20Ukraine%20can%20attack%20targets%20beyond%20visual%20range%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%2C%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bfire%20and%20forget%26quot%3B%3A%20if%20the%20pilot%20has%20to%20break%20the%20radar%20lock%20with%20a%20target%2C%20the%20missile's%20onboard%20radar%20will%20guide%20it.%20Even%20if%20there%20are%20no%20dogfights%20over%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20can%20hunt%20down%20cruise%20missiles%20more%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMultirole%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%204%2C600%20F-16s%20have%20been%20manufactured%20and%20sold%20to%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20countries%20in%20many%20different%20configurations.%20Lockheed%20Martin%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20specific%20capabilities%20of%20the%20aircraft%20being%20sent%20to%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20it%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20the%20F-16%20has%20been%20upgraded%20to%20perform%20many%20missions.%20By%20the%20Gulf%20War%20in%201990%2C%20F-16s%20were%20flying%20regular%20ground-attack%20missions%20with%20missiles%2C%20bombs%20and%20anti-radar%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20MiG-29%20can%20do%20some%20rudimentary%20air-to-ground%20missions%2C%20it's%20not%20made%20for%20the%20task%2C%20said%20Peter%20Layton%2C%20a%20visiting%20fellow%20at%20the%20Griffith%20Asia%20Institute%20and%20former%20Royal%20Australian%20Air%20Force%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20both%20started%20out%20as%20a%20lightweight%20day%20fighter%2C%20but%20because%20Western%20concepts%20evolved...%20(the%20F-16)%20gradually%20evolved%20into%20a%20multirole%20fighter%20capable%20of%20doing%20more%20advanced%20air%20defence%20missions%20as%20well%20as%20ground%20attack%2C%26quot%3B%20Layton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20F-16%20can%20carry%20more%20weapons%20than%20the%20MiG-29%2C%20Su-27%20and%20Su-25%2C%20and%20roughly%20as%20much%20as%20Ukraine's%20tactical%20bomber%2C%20the%20Su-24.%20The%20versions%20being%20sent%20to%20Ukraine%20most%20likely%20have%20an%20upgraded%20version%20of%20the%20AN%2FAPG-66%20radar%2C%20said%20Kelly%20Grieco%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Stimson%20Center.%20It%20can%20keep%20tabs%20on%20targets%20on%20the%20air%20and%20ground%2C%20with%20an%20air-to-air%20range%20past%20100km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20aircraft%20can%20spot%20Ukraine's%20MiG-29s%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20further%20away%20than%20the%20Ukrainians%20can%20spot%20Russian%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20Grieco%20said.%20The%20more%20powerful%20F-16%20radars%20will%20reduce%20the%20radar%20disadvantage%20but%20%26quot%3Bwill%20not%20close%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EF-16s%2C%20and%20Western%20aircraft%20in%20general%2C%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20pilot-friendly%2C%20with%20intuitive%20controls%20and%20displays%20that%20allow%20fliers%20to%20keep%20their%20heads%20up%2C%20Tannehill%20added%2C%20calling%20MiG-29%20and%20Su-27%20cockpits%20%26quot%3Bhopelessly%20out%20of%20date%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Challenges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMiG-29s%2C%20and%20many%20Soviet-era%20fighter%20designs%2C%20were%20meant%20to%20operate%20in%20poor%20runway%20conditions%2C%20and%20have%20shutters%20that%20drop%20down%20over%20their%20air%20intakes%20to%20prevent%20the%20engines%20from%20sucking%20in%20debris%20when%20the%20plane%20is%20on%20the%20ground.%20The%20F-16's%20underslung%20intake%20does%20not%20have%20such%20protections%2C%20and%20it%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20operate%20in%20austere%20conditions%2C%20Grieco%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20F-16%20is%20kind%20of%20a%20precious%20aircraft%2C%20it's%20fragile%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20aircraft%20that%20needs%20a%20long%20runway%2C%20and%20the%20runway%20is%20smooth.%20But%20they're%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20(Ukrainian%20pilots)%20have%20been%20doing%20distributed%20operations...This%20is%20not%20an%20aircraft%20that%20can%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20compensate%2C%20Ukrainian%20forces%20must%20perform%20careful%20sweeps%20of%20runway%20surfaces%2C%20a%20challenging%20proposition%20amid%20a%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraining%20enough%20pilots%20and%20support%20crew%20to%20operate%20the%20new%20fleet%20will%20take%20many%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEight%20pilots%20and%2065%20support%20personnel%20are%20in%20the%20first%20stages%20of%20learning%20how%20to%20operate%20the%20F-16%20in%20Denmark%3B%20others%20are%20in%20Arizona%20and%20the%20southeastern%20Romanian%20town%20of%20Fetesti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20exact%20number%20of%20aircraft%20has%20not%20been%20disclosed%2C%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20in%20the%20dozens%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20inexperienced%20pilots%2C%20the%20first%20step%20is%20familiarization%20with%20the%20new%20aircraft%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20in%20a%20classroom.%20Those%20elements%2C%20plus%20simulator%20time%2C%20will%20last%20about%20three%20weeks%2C%20said%20Layton%2C%20who%20transitioned%20from%20P-3B%20maritime%20patrol%20aircraft%20to%20F-111%20bombers%20during%20his%20career.%20The%20next%20step%20is%20to%20ease%20into%20flying%20over%20the%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20basic%20daytime%20flying%20has%20met%20instructors'%20expectations%2C%20students%20would%20move%20into%20night-time%2C%20bad%20weather%20and%20instrument%20flying%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20lot%20more%20technical%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAir%20combat%20would%20come%20next%2C%20with%20six%20to%20eight%20weeks%20of%20instruction.%20Air-to-ground%20training%20would%20last%20another%20two%20months%2C%20he%20said.%20After%20basic%20instruction%2C%20U.S.%20and%20NATO%20pilots%20spend%20months%20learning%20how%20to%20carry%20out%20more%20specialized%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20enough%20just%20to%20train%20them%20to%20do%20the%20basics%20if%20you%20want%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20those%20aircraft.%20You're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20train%20them%20to%20do%20the%20complex%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20Tannehill%20said%2C%20such%20as%20coordinating%20with%20ground%20units%20or%20flying%20multi-aircraft%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20for%20experienced%20pilots%2C%20learning%20new%20systems%20can%20be%20tough%2C%20Grieco%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20talk%20to%20fighter%20pilots%2C%20they%20talk%20about%20muscle%20memory%3A%20'I%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20something%20where%20I%20don't%20think%2C%20where's%20the%20button%3F'%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20people%20who%20have%20split%20seconds%20to%20make%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELanguage%20could%20be%20an%20issue%20for%20fliers%20without%20much%20English%20experience.%20%26quot%3BSeveral%26quot%3B%20pilots%20and%20dozens%20of%20maintenance%20personnel%20are%20getting%20language%20instruction%20before%20training%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpare%20parts%2C%20manuals%20and%20supplies%20for%20the%20F-16s%20should%20be%20plentiful%2C%20and%20the%20jet%20is%20still%20in%20production%2C%20Farley%20said.%20Only%20about%201%2C600%20MiG-29s%20were%20ever%20produced%2C%20and%20the%20aircraft%20are%20on%20their%20way%20out%20even%20in%20Russia%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Royal%20United%20Service%20Institute%20(RUSI)%20report%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell-trained%20maintenance%20crews%20are%20crucial%2C%20as%20keeping%20F-16s%20in%20the%20fight%20will%20require%20regular%20work-perhaps%20more%20than%20usual%20if%20they%20are%20operating%20in%20difficult%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoren%20Sorenson%2C%20a%20former%20Danish%20F-16%20pilot%2C%20said%20maintenance%20needs%20would%20mean%20each%20aircraft%20would%20be%20flyable%2025%25-50%25%20of%20the%20time.%20Layton%20estimated%20that%20each%20jet%20would%20require%20about%2020%20maintenance%20hours%20between%20flights%20and%20that%20daily%2C%20about%2025%20of%20every%2040%20would%20be%20ready%20to%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Weapons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20United%20States%20began%20supplying%20Ukraine%20with%20AGM-88%20High-speed%20Anti-Radiation%20Missiles%20(HARM)%2C%20a%20weapon%20designed%20to%20home%20in%20on%20and%20destroy%20enemy%20radar%20systems.%20Introduced%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20it%20was%20never%20meant%20to%20be%20used%20with%20anything%20other%20than%20Western%20aircraft.%20But%20by%20attaching%20a%20U.S.%20weapons%20pylon%20to%20a%20Ukrainian%20pylon%2C%20the%20missile%20was%20made%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20made%20a%20quick%20impact%2C%20catching%20Russian%20radar%20operators%20off%20guard%20and%20forcing%20them%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20war%2C%20to%20be%20careful%20about%20when%20and%20where%20they%20operated%2C%20Tannehill%20said.%20However%2C%20the%20HARMs%20had%20to%20be%20programmed%20on%20the%20ground%20to%20fly%20to%20certain%20coordinates.%20If%20there%20was%20nothing%20to%20lock%20onto%20when%20they%20arrived%2C%20the%20missiles%20landed%20harmlessly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20F-16%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20dynamically%20program%20them%20in%20flight.%20The%20HARM%2C%20you%20can%20use%20the%20full%20potential%20because%20you%20can%20change%20the%20instructions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EF-16s%20also%20allow%20Ukraine%20to%20upgrade%20its%20air-to-air%20capabilities%2C%20Layton%20said.%20Ukraine's%20radar-guided%20air-to-air%20missile%20inventory%20is%20centred%20on%20the%20R-27%20model%20-%20introduced%20in%20the%20early%201980s.%20It%20uses%20%26quot%3Bsemi-active%20radar%26quot%3B%20guidance%2C%20in%20which%20the%20launch%20aircraft's%20sensors%20guide%20it%20to%20the%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20the%20fire-and-forget%20AMRAAM%20and%20its%20longer%20range%20-%20the%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20lists%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%2020%20miles%26quot%3B%20and%20Ukraine%20Air%20Force%20spokesperson%20Yuriy%20Ihnat%20said%20it%20could%20hit%20targets%20160km%20away%20-%20may%20mean%20Russian%20aircraft%20can%20no%20longer%20shoot%20at%20Ukrainian%20planes%20with%20impunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Future%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIhnat%20said%20he%20did%20not%20expect%20the%20jets%20to%20operate%20in%20Ukraine%20until%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20not%20win%20the%20war%20immediately%2C%20but%20the%20F-16%20is%20capable%20of%20changing%20the%20course%20of%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20warned%20against%20delivering%20F-16s%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20with%20its%20ambassador%20to%20Denmark%20saying%20in%20August%20that%20doing%20so%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Ban%20escalation%20of%20the%20conflict%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20effects%2C%20Tannehill%20said%2C%20would%20be%20evident%20not%20in%20months%2C%20but%20in%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20F-16s%20are%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20necessary%20to%20continue%20to%20have%20a%20viable%20air%20force%20going%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20preparing%20for%20a%20future%20with%20NATO%2C%20it's%20modernizing...%20it's%20an%20infusion%20of%20fresh%20airframes.%20And%20that's%20going%20to%20be%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702605840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fk7bh13v8_f16-us-air-base-reuters-correct-picture-_625x300_15_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-how-f-16-jets-can-reshape-ukraines-aerial-battlefield-4676834%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20U.S.-made%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20for%20Ukraine%20arrive%20at%20training%20centres%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Europe%2C%20Kyiv's%20allies%20hop