h%E2%80%99s%20Mathura%20by%20a%20court-appointed%20and%20monitored%20advocate%20commissioner%20in%20response%20to%20petitions%20filed%20by%20Hindutva%20outfits%20which%20claim%20that%20the%20mosque%20stands%20on%20the%20place%20where%20Lord%20Krishna%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20has%20allowed%20our%20plea%20for%20appointment%20of%20a%20commission%20to%20survey%20the%20site.%20More%20details%20will%20be%20out%20when%20the%20order%20is%20uploaded%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fkrishna-janmabhoomi-land-dispute-case-allahabad-hc-survey-of-shahi-idgah-mosque-9068116%2F%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ranjana%20Agnihotri%2C%20counsel%20for%20petitioners%2C%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20survey%20of%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%2C%20the%20survey%20of%20the%2017th-century%20mosque%20is%20to%20ascertain%20the%20claims%20being%20made%20by%20Hindutva%20groups%20that%20the%20mosque%20was%20built%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Krishna%20Janmasthal%20(believed%20to%20be%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Lord%20Krishna)%20after%20demolishing%20Katra%20Keshav%20Dev%20Temple.%20The%20temple%20side%20claims%20that%20the%20entire%20tract%20of%20contested%20land%20%E2%80%93%20about%2013.37%20acres%20%E2%80%93%20belongs%20to%20it%20and%20the%20mosque%20should%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20site.%20According%20to%20the%20petitioners%2C%20Katra%20Keshav%20Dev%20Temple%20was%20demolished%20by%20Mughal%20Emperor%20Aurangzeb.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVishnu%20Shankar%20Jain%2C%20another%20advocate%20for%20the%20petitioners%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20has%20allowed%20our%20demand%20that%20an%20advocate%20commissioner%20must%20be%20appointed.%20Who%20will%20be%20the%20advocate%20commissioner%2C%20what%20will%20the%20modalities%20be%2C%20and%20whether%20it%20will%20be%20a%20three-member%20committee%3F%20All%20these%20things%20will%20be%20decided%20on%20December%2018.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20demanded%20that%20in%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%20mosque%2C%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20signs%20and%20symbols%2C%20and%20to%20know%20the%20actual%20factual%20position%2C%20an%20actual%20advocate%20commissioner%20is%20required.%20The%20court%20has%20allowed%20our%20application.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%2018%20separate%20pleas%20were%20filed%20in%20various%20courts%20of%20Mathura%20seeking%20full%20ownership%20of%20the%2013.37-acre%20land%20to%20the%20temple%20management.%20The%20high%20court%20had%20clubbed%20all%20pleas%20and%20transferred%20them%20to%20itself%20for%20adjudicating%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20support%20of%20their%20claims%2C%20these%20groups%20say%20that%20there%20are%20carvings%20of%20lotuses%20on%20some%20walls%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20as%20well%20as%20shapes%20supposedly%20resembling%20Sheshnag%20%E2%80%93%20the%20snake%20demigod%20in%20Hindu%20mythology.%20This%2C%20they%20say%2C%20proves%20their%20point%20that%20the%20mosque%20was%20indeed%20built%20after%20demolishing%20the%20temple%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fin-mathuras-krishna-janmabhoomi-land-dispute-court-gives-nod-for-survey-4672258%5C%22%3ENDTV%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mosque%20side%20had%20earlier%20moved%20the%20high%20court%20praying%20for%20the%20quashing%20of%20petitions%20citing%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20of%201991%2C%20which%20maintains%20the%20religious%20status%20of%20any%20place%20of%20worship%20as%20it%20was%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20in%201968%2C%20both%20the%20temple%20side%20(Shri%20Krishna%20Janmasthan%20Seva%20Sansthan)%20and%20the%20mosque%20side%20(Shahi%20Masjid%20Idgah%20Trust)%20inked%20an%20agreement%20to%20the%20effect%20that%2010.9%20acres%20from%20the%20total%2013.37%20acres%20would%20be%20of%20the%20temple%E2%80%99s%20property%20while%202.5%20acres%20would%20belong%20to%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muslim%20side%20is%20expected%20to%20challenge%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702552516000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25112937%2FSEM1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkrishna-janmabhoomi-case-allahabad-hc-orders-survey-of-shahi-idgah-mosque-in-mathura%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20survey%20of%20the%2017th-century%20mosque%20is%20to%20ascertain%20the%20claims%20being%20made%20by%20Hindutva%20groups%20that%20the%20mosque%20was%20built%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Krishna%20Janmasthal%20(believed%20to%20be%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Lord%20Krishna)%20after%20demolishing%20Katra%20Keshav%20Dev%20Temple.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkrishna-janmabhoomi-case-allahabad-hc-orders-survey-of-shahi-idgah-mosque-in-mathura%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mushy%20K-dramas%20to%20watch%20this%20holiday%20season%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702549800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105981050%2Cimgsize-.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fcrash-landing-on-you-goblin-lovestruck-in-the-city-five-mushy-korean-dramas-that-will-warm-you-up-this-holiday-season%2Fphotostory%2F105981050.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Crash%20Landing%20on%20You%2C%20Goblin%2C%20Lovestruck%20in%20the%20City%3A%20FIVE%20mushy%20Korean%20dramas%20that%20will%20warm%20you%20up%20this%20holiday%20season!%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Amaat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14154242%2FScreenshot-2023-12-14-at-3.40.36.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Amaat%20(285%2C221%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20literal%20meaning%20of%20Amaat%20tells%20us%20nothing%20about%20the%20caste.%20One%20of%20the%20dictionary%20meanings%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98amaat%E2%80%99%20is%20someone%20who%20has%20never%20been%20defeated.%20But%20that%20meaning%20does%20not%20suit%20the%20reality%20of%20this%20caste%20group.%20This%20is%20because%20if%20it%20was%20true%2C%20they%20would%20be%20treated%20like%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20of%20the%20Hindu%20religion.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20they%20were%20considered%20Brahmins%20who%20had%20remained%20undefeated%20for%20centuries%20%E2%80%93%20except%20in%20the%20battle%20of%20Bhima-Koregaon%20in%201818.%20It%20is%20also%20possible%20that%20they%20were%20once%20warriors%20like%20the%20Rajputs.%20But%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20present%20social%20status%2C%20all%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20look%20down%20upon%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20359px)%2085vw%2C%20359px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22359%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22514%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20who%20are%20the%20Amaats%3F%20Are%20they%20really%20Brahmins%20ostracised%20by%20superior%20Brahmins%3F%20Or%20are%20they%20Rajputs%20who%20have%20been%20sidelined%20by%20the%20ruling%20Rajputs%20themselves%3F%20There%20is%20no%20information%20available%20about%20this%20caste%20in%20history.%20The%20ethnographic%20study%20of%20this%20caste%20also%20does%20not%20offer%20any%20clear%20conclusions.%20Sometimes%20it%20appears%20as%20if%20their%20existence%20is%20part%20of%20a%20conspiracy%20theory.%20This%20is%20because%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20are%20generally%20not%20poor%20%E2%80%93%20except%20a%20few.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocially%2C%20the%20Brahmins%20and%20Rajputs%20may%20treat%20them%20as%20inferior%20and%20not%20mix%20with%20them%20or%20form%20matrimonial%20alliances%20but%20ordinary%20Amaats%20consider%20themselves%20equal%20to%20these%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20groups%20in%20status.%20In%20Bihar%20they%20are%20included%20in%20the%20backward%20class%20group%20and%20enjoy%20the%20benefits%20of%20reservation.%20But%20they%20are%20not%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20find%20themselves%20in%20such%20a%20scenario.%20The%20Nautiyals%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20also%20consider%20themselves%20Brahmins%2C%20but%20are%20under%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20category.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20who%20are%20they%20really%3F%20The%20name%20Amaat%20might%20also%20be%20a%20corruption%20of%20the%20word%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98amaatya%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20means%20%E2%80%98companion%E2%80%99.%20A%20companion%20can%20be%20of%20two%20types%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20king.%20One%20is%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20security%20guard%20and%20the%20other%20is%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20minister.%20%E2%80%98Amaatya%E2%80%99%20also%20means%20%E2%80%98minister%E2%80%99.%20During%20the%20time%20of%20Chandragupta%20Maurya%2C%20Chanakya%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98Amaatya%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20theory%20does%20not%20shed%20light%20on%20who%20the%20Amaat%20are.%20If%20they%20are%20security%20guards%2C%20they%20might%20be%20Rajput%20and%20if%20they%20are%20ministers%2C%20they%20might%20be%20connected%20to%20Brahmins.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20thoughtfully%20crafted%20secret.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMegasthenes%20has%20written%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20them.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20doors%20to%20reach%20higher%20positions%20were%20closed%20for%20people%20of%20lower%20castes.%20Only%20people%20from%20a%20professional%20class%20were%20appointed%20to%20the%20judiciary%20and%20executive.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Katyayan%20also%20emphasised%2C%20%E2%80%9CAmaatya%20should%20be%20of%20Brahmin%20caste%20only.%20Amaatya%20means%20minister%2C%20which%20is%20made%20up%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emantrin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emantrin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20means%20mantra%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMundakupanishad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Amaatra%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20the%20fourth%20state%20of%20meditation%2C%20which%20is%20also%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esamadhi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20inconsistencies%20in%20this%20theory.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20concept%20of%20Nirguna%20or%20god%20being%20non-dual%20has%20not%20existed%20in%20Hinduism.%20In%20this%20religion%2C%20body%20and%20soul%20are%20given%20importance%20in%20two%20different%20forms.%20But%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20Nirguna%20and%20Advaita%2C%20one%20can%20say%20that%20those%20Brahmins%20who%20are%20not%20idol%20worshippers%20can%20be%20called%20Amaat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Indian%20and%20foreign%20scholars%20have%20written%20about%20them.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20the%20journal%20published%20by%20Bihar%20and%20Orissa%20Research%20Society%20in%201919%2C%20Amaat%20has%20been%20described%20as%20a%20pure%20priest%20of%20the%20king.%20Earlier%20in%201909%2C%20in%20their%20book%20about%20castes%20in%20India%2C%20Edgar%20Thurston%20and%20K.%20Rangchari%20stated%20that%20Amaats%20do%20not%20eat%20anything%20touched%20even%20by%20upper%20caste%20Brahmins.%20According%20to%20them%2C%20Amaats%20belong%20to%20the%20Shaiva%20sect%20and%20in%20the%20same%20temple%20where%20Jangam%20Brahmins%20(belonging%20to%20the%20Jangam%20Shaiva%20sect%20and%20who%20are%20the%20highest%20class%20Brahmins)%20perform%20the%20duties%20of%20priests%20of%20Shivalinga%2C%20Amaats%20enjoy%20the%20status%20of%20the%20priests%20of%20Bhairava.%20Bhairava%20have%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20Hindu%20mythology.%20Bhairavas%20are%20given%20a%20place%20in%20the%20temple%20premises%20but%20not%20the%20main%20sanctum%20where%20Brahmins%20run%20the%20show.%20The%20property%20of%20the%20Amaat%20also%20lies%20outside%20the%20sanctum%20sanctorum.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Tribes%20and%20Castes%20of%20Bengal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20in%201891%2C%20Risley%20wrote%20that%20Amaats%20served%20as%20domestic%20servants.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKashi%20Prasad%20Jaiswal%2C%20a%20renowned%20historian%20of%20Bihar%2C%20has%20also%20written%20that%20during%20the%2012th%20century%2C%20the%20economics%20and%20the%20tradition%20of%20punishment%20gradually%20weakened%20and%20theology%20became%20dominant.%20Society%20fell%20into%20the%20grip%20of%20hypocrisy.%20He%20opines%20that%20due%20to%20their%20separation%20from%20the%20majority%2C%20%E2%80%98Amaatra%E2%80%99%20may%20have%20become%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20dissenter%2C%20which%20would%20later%20become%20%E2%80%98Amaat%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20while%20theorising%2C%20Jaiswal%20does%20not%20clarify%20that%20the%2012th%20century%20was%20the%20century%20when%20the%20reign%20of%20outside%20rulers%20began%20in%20India.%20It%20can%20be%20assumed%20that%20during%20that%20time%2C%20the%20dominance%20of%20Brahmins%20would%20have%20declined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20why%20would%20any%20Muslim%20ruler%20want%20to%20make%20a%20Brahmin%20his%20Amaat%20%E2%80%93%20minister%20or%20security%20guard%3F%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20Muslim%20rulers%20came%20to%20know%20about%20the%20story%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20commander%20Pushyamitra%20Shunga%20and%20how%20he%20killed%20Brihadratha%20by%20stabbing%20him%20in%20the%20back%20and%20captured%20the%20kingdom%20of%20the%20Maurya%20dynasty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20social%2C%20educational%20and%20economic%20grounds%2C%20Amaat%2C%20with%20a%20population%20of%20285%2C221%2C%20are%20unlike%20other%20backward%20castes%20or%20Dalits%20of%20Bihar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F261400%2Fbihar-caste-survey-who-are-the-amaats%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3EMadaria%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-koeri-kushwaha%5C%22%3EKoeri%2FKushwaha%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%5C%22%3EChaupal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-nai-hajjaam%5C%22%3ENai%2FHajjaam%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-pasi%5C%22%3EPasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-rangrez%5C%22%3ERangrez%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chamar%5C%22%3EChamar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-gorkan%5C%22%3EGorkan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-jutt%5C%22%3EJutt%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0